U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken outlined the Biden administration's China stance during a major policy speech on Thursday. Though the policy stresses on greater coordination and cooperation, it also dwelt at length on America's efforts to out-compete China in the next stages of development. The speech was peppered with words like 'invest, align, and compete', all of which implied that the Biden government would continue to expand domestic investment, further consolidate ties with allies and intensify competition with China. But is this really a fair game? In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Zhu Zhu unveils the hidden agenda of Blinken.